wild season is a 1967 south african drama film directed by emil nofal and starring gert van den bergh , marie du toit and antony thomas . a family operating a trawler off the south african coast , suffer a personal tragedy . the film provoked a backlash in south africa because it was bilingual and featured black actors in leading roles . it was also felt that it portrayed a negative , stereotypical portrayal of afrikaners . a number of scenes were directed by jans rautenbach , because emil nofal suffered from seasickness .